==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Travail
<hw>Trav"ail</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>travail</ets>; cf. Pr. <ets>trabalh</ets>, <ets>trebalh</ets>,
toil, torment, torture; probably from LL. <ets>trepalium</ets> a place
where criminals are tortured, instrument of torture. But the French word
may be akin to L. <ets>trabs</ets> a beam, or have been influenced by a
derivative from <ets>trabs</ets> (cf. <er>Trave</er>). Cf.
<er>Travel</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Labor with pain; severe toil or
exertion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As everything of price, so this doth require
<qex>travail</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Parturition; labor; <as>as, an easy
<ex>travail</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travail</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Travail
<hw>Tra`vail"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>travail</ets>, a frame for confining a horse, or OF.
<ets>travail</ets> beam, and E. <ets>trave</ets>, n. Cf.
<er>Travail</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>Same as
<er>Travois</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Travail
<hw>Trav"ail</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Travailed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Travailing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>travailler</ets>, OF.
<ets>traveillier</ets>, <ets>travaillier</ets>, to labor, toil, torment;
cf. Pr. <ets>trebalhar</ets> to torment, agitate. See <er>Travail</er>,
<pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To labor with pain; to toil.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Slothful persons which will not
<xex>travail</xex> for their livings.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Latimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To suffer the pangs of childbirth; to be in
labor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travail</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Travail
<hw>Trav"ail</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To harass; to tire.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if all these troubles had not been sufficient to
<qex>travail</qex> the realm, a great division fell among the
nobility.</q> <rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travailous</ent>⟦br⟧
